COVID-19 Status 💉 🦠

As of 8:39AM PT yesterday, over 3.7 million Canadians have tested positive for COVID-19. Sadly, 38.7 thousand have died.

In the last day, 4.9 thousand new infections were reported and 6 deaths. Currently 6,523 are in the hospital and 458 are in the ICU. This is trending downwards.

Fortunately, 83.6 million doses of the vaccine have been administered. For those 5 years and older, 92.7% have their 1st shot and 85.5% are fully vaccinated!

Vaccination is speeding up, but there are 11.7 million doses in the freezer. It currently takes ~145 days for new deliveries to get into arms.

At the current rate, Canadians should achieve herd immunity around when 80% of the entire population is fully vaccinated. There is no approved vaccine for children under 5.

  • 81 in 100 have at least one vaccine dose,
    75 in 100 are fully vaccinated.
    37 in 100 have been boosted.
    Herd immunity is estimated at ~85%
